            </rs> The Evidence declared, that having an occasion to go out about some Business, he left the Plate in its usual plate, and his Fellow Servant having occasion to use a pair of Candlesticks, fetch'd a pair away, and returning with them some time after, she mist them that were left behind; then they applied themselves to the Keeper of the Gate-house, who accordingly took them in Hedge-Lane with a parcel of Pick-lock Keys, amongst which was one called a 500 l. Jack: There was another Evidence who declared that he was with Golding and Hearn in the Robbery, and<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="16970519002"></xptr>that Hearn got over the Wall and opened the Door, and he took a Picklock-key and opened the Door where the Goods were, and took them away, and the next Day they went to the George in the Pall-Mall, where Raby was sent for, who came with a pair of Weights and Skales, and gave them 6 l. 2 s. 6 d. for them, and that they told her they were stole, but did not tell her where; they could say but little, and were known to be Offenders, the Jury found them <rs id="t16970519-6-verdict31" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16970519-6-verdict31" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs>.</p>
